comment: Lemma for ~ subfacp1 . In ~ subfacp1lem6 we cut up the set of all derangements on ` 1 ... ( N + 1 ) ` first according to the value at ` 1 ` , and then by whether or not ` ( f `` ( f `` 1 ) ) = 1 ` . In this lemma, we show that the subset of all ` N + 1 ` derangements that satisfy this for fixed ` M = ( f `` 1 ) ` is in bijection with ` N - 1 ` derangements, by simply dropping the ` x = 1 ` and ` x = M ` points from the function to get a derangement on ` K = ( 1 ... ( N - 1 ) ) \ { 1 , M } ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 23-Jan-2015.)
